SequenceNumberProperty.Name: SequenceNumber
SequenceNumberProperty.Description:
Sequence number used to define the task precedence constraints. To model a task sequence that is simply a serially ordered set of tasks, define the tasks with increasing sequence numbers (e.g., the first task is numbered '10', the second task is numbered '20', and so forth). Tasks with identical sequence numbers will be performed in parallel.
For a more in-depth discussion on task sequence numbering including examples of how to model parallel subsequences, please refer to the Task Sequence element documentation.

ExpressionProperty.Name: TaskProcessingTime
ExpressionProperty.Description: The time required to perform the task.

BooleanProperty.Name: ReportStatistics
BooleanProperty.Description: Indicates whether statistics are to be automatically reported for this object or element.

ObjectInstanceProperty.Name: SiteObjectName
ObjectInstanceProperty.Description: The name of the fixed object that is the inventoryâ€™s physical location.

ExpressionProperty.Name: InitialQuantity
ExpressionProperty.Description: The quantity of material present in the inventory at the beginning of the simulation run.

EnumProperty.Name: ReviewPeriod
EnumProperty.Description:
The frequency of inventory review to determine whether a replenishment order is required.
If the review period is â€˜Continuousâ€™, then an inventory review is triggered once at the start of the simulation and then whenever the inventory position decreases.
If the review period is â€˜Timerâ€™, then an inventory review is triggered whenever the specified timer fires its event.

ReplenishmentPolicyProperty.Name: ReplenishmentPolicy
ReplenishmentPolicyProperty.Description: The replenishment policy checked at the time of an inventory review to determine whether a replenishment order is required and, if so, the recommended order size.

ElementProperty.Name: OnReplenishmentOrderProcess
ElementProperty.Description:
The name of the process that will be executed to handle an inventory replenishment order. Note that whenever this process is triggered by the replenishment policy, the inventory's quantity on order will have been automatically increased by the recommended order size.
NOTE: The created token's material order detail reference will provide the detail of the replenishment request. For example, the function Token.MaterialOrderDetail.Quantity may be used to get the recommended order size.
